name: Gawa Christian School
notes: Gäwa Christian School commenced as part of the NT Christian Schools system in 2004 and provides educational opportunities to students from Gäwa and surrounding Homelands.  The school is registered from Transition to Year 10 and has around 35 students enrolled. A community-based ‘play group’ is also run out of the school on 3 mornings per week.  Students at Gäwa Christian School are supported by community Elders as well as the school staff and students have the opportunity to receive quality education on their ancestral lands.
